  "prompt": "How can an email account get hacked?",
  "response": "Here are some common ways an email account can get hacked:\n\n1. Weak passwords\n- Using simple/common passwords\n- Not using complex combinations of letters, numbers, and symbols\n\n2. Phishing attacks\n- Clicking on fake emails that look legitimate\n- Entering login credentials on fraudulent websites\n\n3. Malware and viruses\n- Downloading infected files or attachments\n- Visiting compromised websites\n\n4. Public Wi-Fi vulnerabilities\n- Using unsecured networks\n- Hackers intercepting data transmission\n\n5. Password reuse\n- Using same password across multiple accounts\n- If one account is compromised, others become vulnerable\n\n6. Social engineering tactics\n- Tricking users into revealing login information\n- Manipulating people through personal information\n\n7. Data breaches\n- When company databases are hacked\n- Stolen login credentials sold on dark web\n\n8. Keylogging\n- Malicious software tracking keyboard inputs\n- Capturing login credentials\n\n9. Inadequate security settings\n- Not using two-factor authentication\n- Not updating security questions\n\n10. Unauthorized device access\n- Someone physically accessing logged-in device\n- Not logging out of shared computers\n\nProtecting against these risks involves using strong passwords, enabling two-factor authentication, being cautious online, and regularly updating security settings.",
